{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3c48e8b5-d498-4784-9fd7-9a5bf3bb7999","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|--------|-------------|\n| App launch | Created → Activated |\n| User switches away | Deactivated → Stopped |\n| User returns | Resumed → Activated |\n| App closed | Stopped → Destroying |\n\n`Backgrounding` is iOS/Mac Catalyst–specific (lets you save state before suspension).\n\nReplace `Debug.WriteLine` with your preferred logger (e.g., `ILogger`, Serilog) for production diagnostics.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ed508a4c-f63a-44db-9ed7-3711030857fd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about Window lifecycle events in .NET MAUI and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI that I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":420,"requestId":"4839:2ADC27:74B2B31:8106C94:69F3FB07"},"id":"559d8734-1344-4376-bc55-5b1ffd6ca406","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:00.651Z","parentId":"f76cf499-6f8e-40ad-b2d4-ee247dc850bb"}
